The paper focuses on developing high-performance algorithms for sparse matrix-matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental operation in many computational applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Architecture (cs.AR), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
